<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<appendix xml:id="app-r-markdown" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Reproducible Reporting: R Markdown</title>

  <introduction>
    <p>
      This appendix covers reproducible reporting using R Markdown, an
      alternative to Quarto that is widely used in the R community. R Markdown
      allows you to combine narrative text, R code, and output into a single
      document that can be rendered to HTML, PDF, Word, and other formats.
    </p>
  </introduction>

